00:20:45.660 --> 00:20:49.220
And then, it's going to take off
like a shot. So,

00:20:49.220 --> 00:20:53.180
this is the repulsive energy term.
And so, what's the net energy?

00:20:53.180 --> 00:20:57.560
The net energy is the sum of the
repulsive and the attractive.

00:20:57.560 --> 00:21:01.930
And, see, out at very, very high
separations, it's essentially all

00:21:01.930 --> 00:21:06.300
repulsive, excuse me,
all attractive. And at very,

00:21:06.300 --> 00:21:10.680
very low separations, it's all
repulsive. And in between,

00:21:10.680 --> 00:21:15.050
it goes through a minimum. And,
this minimum here is what gives us

00:21:15.050 --> 00:21:19.430
the value of the inter-electrode
separation, the inter-ion separation.

00:21:19.430 --> 00:21:23.810
And so, I need to cheat a little
